# App Color Palette

All UI colors must come from `frontend/constants/colors.ts`. Never hardcode hex values in components.

## Light mode tokens

| Token | Hex | Use |
|-------|-----|-----|
| `background` | `#F6F8FB` | Page background |
| `primary` | `#2563EB` | Main buttons, navbar, links |
| `success` | `#10B981` | Success / active states |
| `text` | `#0F172A` | Primary text |
| `card` | `#FFFFFF` | Cards, sidebar surface |
| `border` | `#E2E8F0` | Borders, dividers |

## How to use in code

```tsx
// Preferred — respects light/dark mode
import { useAppColors } from '@/hooks/use-app-colors';
const colors = useAppColors();

// Paper components — use theme (mapped from AppColors)
import { useTheme } from 'react-native-paper';
const theme = useTheme();
theme.colors.primary;   // #2563EB light
theme.colors.background;
theme.colors.outline;   // border

// Static reference / theme setup only
import { AppColors, Palette } from '@/constants/colors';
```

## Rules

- Add new colors to `constants/colors.ts` first, then wire through `paper-theme.ts`
- Use `useAppColors()` or `useTheme()` from Paper — never inline `#2563EB` etc.
- Dark mode variants live in `AppColors.dark` — keep light tokens as the brand source of truth
